        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as Thenius asserts) expansion of “The Lord would not destroy Judah, for the sake of David his servant” (Kings).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The covenant that he had made with David.—Literally, for David. So Isaiah 55:3, “I will make an everlasting covenant for you, even the sure mercies of David.” This construction is generally used of the stronger imposing conditions on the weaker. (Comp. Joshua 9:6; 1Samuel 11:1-2.) In the Pentateuch, God makes a covenant with (im or eth) His people (Genesis 15:16; Exodus 24:8).",
